  "body": "Description:\nOn Windows, skill detection fails for skills that require CLI binaries (e.g., blogwatcher, yt-dlp, ffmpeg) because `/src/infra/binaries.ts` uses the `which` command, which is not native to Windows. Windows uses `where.exe` instead.\n\nOther parts of the codebase (e.g., `onboard-helpers.ts`, `exec-approvals.ts`) correctly use `where` on Windows, but `binaries.ts` does not.\n\nExpected behavior:\n- Skills requiring binaries should be detected on Windows using `where` instead of `which`\n- Installing `which` for Windows AND creating symlinks without `.exe` extension (e.g., `mklink blogwatcher -> blogwatcher.exe`)\n\nAffected file:\n- `/src/infra/binaries.ts` (line ~11 uses `exec(\"which\", [name])`)",
